<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9984053968517></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9984053968517><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=12&mid=9984053968517>RE: Playing the Mage</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>363 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 21st 10:49 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>"Fact is most groups prefer Wizards for nuking and consider your pet a nuisance."<br><br>That my friend is not a fact, that is your opinion. Whenver I played my non-mage characters I would always take a magician over a wizard. Why? Becuase magicians do more damage over time than wizards. Wizards may do damage faster, but you don't NEED them to do damage faster. If they start doing a lot of damage they will get aggroed on and killed.<br><br>As for quests, yes magicians have the least amount of quests. However you are inncorect in saying that they can't start them until level 40. Magicians can start their focus item quests as early as level 12 by getting help from higher level players (the items you need for the focus item quests will be GIVEN to you by higher level players becuase they won't have much use for them).<br><br>Oh and BTW, magicians require no more thinking to play than any other caster. In fact, magacians require less thinking and strategy to play than many other casters.<br><br>Former EQ Addict.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
